    "id": "24-parson-street-townhouse",
    "title": "The Crafted Edge",
    "category": "Residential",
    "location": "24 Parson, Kensington",
    "year": 2026,
    "status": "Completed",
    "service": "Multi Townhouse Development",
    "area": "325.48 sqm",
    "summary": "325.48 square metres of site forced the hand of this Kensington development toward verticality almost as a matter of necessity. Where horizontal expansion simply wasn't available, stacking a sequence of efficient, generously proportioned spaces through the section. This vertical strategy does more than solve a spatial problem, it fundamentally shapes the experience of living within the building, with each level offering a distinct relationship to light, outlook, and privacy as one moves up through the home. Referencing the suburb's heritage vocabulary of masonry terraces, modest cottages, and industrial structures, the material palette is intentionally robust and understated. Rich textures, carefully crafted detailing, and a considered composition of openings create a façade that feels both familiar and contemporary.",
