    "year": 2026,
    "status": "Completed",
    "service": "Residential",
    "area": "654 sqm",
    "summary": "It has the luxury of working at a different scale, and the design capitalises on this freedom through spatial sequencing rather than sheer size alone. The home is organised as a series of proportioned volumes, each carefully calibrated to frame a different relationship to light, landscape, or view. Rather than a single grand gesture, the architecture unfolds gradually, with movement through the home structured as a sequence of discoveries, room by room, threshold by threshold. This sequencing is central to the project's identity. As occupants move through the home, the changing quality of light, the shifting proportions of each space, and the varying degrees of enclosure and openness combine to create a rhythm that feels considered rather than incidental. Material restraint underpins this experience, a disciplined palette that avoids ornament in favour of clarity, allowing proportion, light, and spatial sequencing to carry the architectural narrative.",
