  {
    "id": "31-gent-street-yarraville-townhouse",
    "title": "Gently Curve",
    "category": "Residential",
    "location": "31 Gent",
    "year": 2026,
    "status": "Completed",
    "service": "Townhouse Development",
    "area": "236.90 sqm",
    "summary": "Curved geometry replaces the orthogonal habits of conventional residential planning, a deliberate departure from the rectilinear logic that typically governs townhouse design. Sweeping walls soften transitions between spaces, while a sculptural, curved staircase becomes a genuine centrepiece, an architectural moment in its own right rather than a purely functional element of vertical circulation. This curvature actively shapes how the home is experienced, guiding movement through the plan in a way that feels continuous rather than compartmentalised, and creating moments of discovery as sightlines shift and reveal new spaces around each sweeping wall. Large openings extend this spatial logic outward, establishing a strong and deliberate connection to the adjoining reserve. The integration of panoramic outlooks, fluid circulation, and sculpted forms, the dwelling moves beyond conventional residential planning to create a home defined by movement, openness, and a distinctive architectural identity.",
