  {
    "id": "87-93-elm-park-drive-commercial",
    "title": "Elm Developed",
    "category": "Commercial",
    "location": "87-93 Elm Park",
    "year": 2026,
    "status": "Completed",
    "service": "Commercial Development",
    "area": "6,397.10 sqm",
    "summary": "An irregular 6,397 square metre site presented a significant planning challenge, and Elm Developed's response is one of discipline rather than dramatic gesture. The irregularity of the site geometry could easily have produced an awkward, compromised building form, but instead the design uses this complexity as an opportunity to refine rather than complicate, resulting in a workplace environment built on efficiency and clarity rather than architectural excess. The façade's identity is established through refined detailing and careful proportion rather than complexity for its own sake, a considered composition of solids, openings, and material transitions that achieves visual interest without relying on ornamental gesture. This restraint carries through to the building's massing, which is calibrated to maximise development yield while still presenting a coherent and legible presence within its surrounding context. Internally, the brief prioritises the practical realities of contemporary commercial occupancy: daylight penetration, spatial flexibility, and occupant amenity are treated as core design drivers rather than secondary considerations. The result is a building that balances commercial pragmatism with genuine architectural quality, a considered response to a difficult site that resists the temptation to over-design its way around the constraint.",
